Package fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.ssqueue

DEVS simulation example: HIOA models with value histories.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Client
    The class Client defines a simple client in a simulation of a single server queue model M/M/1.
    ClientGeneratorModel
    The class ClientGeneratorModel implements a simulation which exports and generates client arrival events.
    ClientGeneratorModel.ClientGeneratorReport
    The class ClientGeneratorReport implements the simulation report for the client generator model.
    EndServiceClient
    The class EndServiceClient implements the end of service event.
    GeneratedClientArrival
    The class GeneratedClient implements a client arrival event as seen from the client generator model side.
    ServerModel
    The class ServerModel implements the server role in a simulation of a M/M/1 single server queue model.
    ServerModel.ServerReport
    The class ServerReport implement the simulation report for the server model by returning the statistics computed during the simulation run i.e., the average total or sojourn time of clients in the system.
    ServerSideClientArrival
    The class ServerSideClientArrival implements a client arrival event as seen from the server model side.
    SimulationMain
    The class SimulationMain runs a simulation for the single-server queue example.
    SSQueueCoupledES_Model
    The class SSQueueCoupledES_Model implements a coupled model for the example.
    SSQueueCoupledES_Model.SSQueueReport
    The class SSQueueReport implements the simulation report for the single-server queue example.

Package fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.ssqueue Description

DEVS simulation example: HIOA models with value histories.

This package provides a first DEVS simulation example using the event scheduling approach. It is a simple single-server simulation model keeping the server and the client generator models separated.
